caption: I like this little spot. Food was great! I had shrimp with mushrooms,  and asparagus. To top it off a glass of red sangria.  Ended the night very well. The employees were welcoming. Will make my way back there one day in the near future.
Loved it!

It was our first indoor dining experience in will over a year (since 2019, actually) and was excellent! We went for my partner's birthday, and truly had a wonderful meal. The calamari was melt in your mouth (which is a phrase I never would have thought could describe calamari). My seafood stew was excellent and my partner enjoyed his salmon. The creme brulee was perfectly textured and we took a couple cannoli home for a snack! Will be back!

We had the server “Kay” tonight. Who never introduced herself, never presented the specials, and was extremely out of it. My partner and I both have come here before and just loved our experience. However, tonight was such a disappointment because of our waitress. She was so out of it. If anyone comes here, make sure to not have her as your server.
I'm  a Bethesda native son, but been living, hunting and fishing in Alaska for more than 20 years now. Tony's is the place I come to enjoy  fish when I come back to the "city." The best!

Finally got over to Chef Tony's for some HEMI pizza yesterday. So good ... and absolutely worth the drive from Gaithersburg.  We tried 3 pizzas: the veggie, the cupped pepperoni, and the cheese. Hard to choose a favorite. Our little ones can be picky when it comes to pizza and even they enjoyed it.  It’s just as described: tons of high-quality flavorful cheese, pillowy dough, and a deliciously crispy border and crust. My wife likened it to focaccia bread. We got the sauce on the side and used it for dipping – lots of flavor in that sauce, too! We were a little skeptical about the size, but these pizzas are SUBSTANTIAL. Big punch. Highly recommended. One more reason to love Chef Tony's. :)

The first time I went with my daughter, we were eating when she noticed a piece of metal in her food.  It was from a cleaning utensil they used in the kitchen. Tonight, we ordered pizza.  We live half a mile away, and despite the fact that staff has told us our pizza was out for delivery 40 minutes ago, we still have not received it. I'm over it.
Best calamari in Bethesda!

Chef Tony makes PIZZA!!!! Detroit style Hemi pizza and it is delicious. Crisp crust yet soft and chewy. Melted cheese and Tomato sauce shimmied on top. It literally melts in your mouth $16 with crisp pepperonis. Try it TODAY!!!! Pics to follow.

It can be hectic on Valentine's Day in a restaurant even when it is not a pandemic. Chef Tony and his staff were clearly trying as hard as they could to make everyone happy, from the lucky few who got dine-in reservations to the many, many to-go orders. The food was fabulous, and, while it took a bit longer than was our previous experience at the establishment, it was prepared and served with care. My grilled caesar salad and chicken piccata tasted just as lovingly prepared as they had previously, and my date's cream of crab soup and parmesan crusted cod were delectable. The chocolate sin cake to finish it off was maybe the best part, but it is hard to say when everything was so tasty. We will definitely return, and look forward to being made to feel so welcome again.

WORST DINNER EXPERIENCE IN MY LIFE. If you want to get COVID or freeze, I recommend you to come here to dinner.  1. We were having dinner wearing coats. 2. Door was opened during all the time that we were there. Breeze of 34F coming inside, directly to our table. 3. About 15 people around us, without saving the minimum distance as you can see in the picture.  Makes me SO MAD to have to pay an expensive bill having this MISERABLE DINNER.  OUR FIRST AND LAST TIME HERE.  The only good thing was the waitress, she was nice.

Food was good. We were put right next to the door. There were at least 15 people huddled around our table waiting for their to-go food. Some of them waited for most of the time we were at the table. There was a crowd outside, also waiting for their to go orders. The other guests held the door open for the cold to come in and we were forced to wear our coats at the table in order to stay warm. We asked to be moved to a different table immediately after arriving. We were told there are no more tables available in the back. After a quick walk to the restroom, there were plenty of open tables. If the justification for the open tables is COVID, it’s obviously much better to have a crowd of people around our table waiting hours for their to go food. The dine in experience was miserable and judging on what it’s like to take away, this is the first and last time we’ll eat here.  Also, the host at the front door is a cranky old man who was rude to everyone he spoke with.

I normally love this place. Every time I’ve been the food has been amazing (no matter what I got). So when they announced Detroit style pizza, I was excited to try.  Tried this style of pizza recently at Caddies and fell in love. Very disappointed ordering from here. Got it to go, brought it home and undercooked, not crispy on the sides and all around soggy. Will still come back to Chef Tony’s but will not get the pizza again.

We usually order a seafood dinner from Chef Tony's, but tonight we tried the Detroit pizza. Fabulous! Delicious blend of cheese on a buttery crust, easily served two, along with a side of the brussel sprouts. Will definitely order again. So happy to be able to support one of our favorite local businesses.
One of my favorite restaurants. Everything is top notch.  The crab soup is astounding!

It was a fantastic Feast of the Seven Fishes at home! It included fish paste with bread, herring salad, scallops soup, sautéed mussels, shrimp kabob, whole grilled branzino, clams pasta, and three desserts: Chef Sonia’s cheesecake, chocolate sin cake and tiramisu.
Crab cakes
Best crab cake I've had! No fillers, just crab meat, seasoning and other simple ingredients. Can't wait for the pandemic to be over so I can truly have the full dining experience.
We ordered takeout tonight and it was made promptly and the food was outstanding! What a treasure of a place. Highly recommend!

We were very please with our 3 course NYE dinner for 2 package! Everything was delicious, especially the cream of crab soup and scallops. We were a little surprised to find the lobster dinner was in fact a whole lobster! We would recommend, if you have any questions, you ask ahead of time to make sure you're prepared to pick a lobster. Aside from that little surprise, everything was marvelous!
This spot simply knows how to serve their customers. Consistently with a very kind demeanor. The food is conveniently priced, constantly delightful and neat.
The best food I have ever had! Everything we got was delicious and the restaurant is super cute.
Delicious!

I ordered Thanksgiving dinner here. My pickup time was 11 am and I was a little early. The meal was ready and delivered right to my car. I heated it up later. It was very tasty. I deducted one star ⭐ because the green beans were too al dente for my tastes and there was a thin but obvious bone in the turkey. Otherwise, the meal was flavorful and very enjoyable.
Consistently excellent food, reasonable prices and outstanding service by friendly staff!
The food is fantastic! The service exceptional. I will definitely come back. While a small restaurant they followed all covid guidelines and i felt very conformable.
Great food, great service!
I meant to add your crab soup is a killer. I am addicted instantly.👍
We love Chef Tony’s! The portions are generous, the ingredients are always fresh, and his food is delicious and inventive. It’s our go-to restaurant for special events and holidays.
I just wanted to  say  thank you for the way my wife and I were treated at your restaurant.  The experience was fantastic and I would highly recommend your restaurant to anyone who asks.

One of the best meals I've ever had in my life.  Pan seared tuna with perfect crunch/cooked on the outside and soft in middle.  I don't even know what the sauce was that came with it but it was spectacular,  ultra thin french fries crunchy and salty contrasted with flavorful asparagus

Third time ordering dinner delivery from Chef Tony's.  All three experiences were great.  Favorites were the Maine Lobster Pasta and Spicy Shrimp pasta dish.  Liked the stuff mushroom appetizer as well.  It has been a great place to order from for restaurant dining at home during the COVID crisis.  I've also dined in at Chef Tony's in the past and the food was good as well.  I stayed away from ordering fried food, such as calamari/zucchini appetizers for home delivery because that (fried) food doesn't tend to taste as good as delivery.  I find the prices are generally reasonable given the generous portions.
A fine meal, a quiet place and inside service even in these trying times.
One of the BEST food and dining experiences in the DMV. I have enjoyed many meals here, their takeout and carry out is also stellar.
(Translated by Google) Because it is a very nice place, very quiet and you eat quite well  (Original) Porq es un lugar muy agradable, muy tranquilo y se come bastante bien
First time visiting the restaurant and we were very impressed.  Food was delicious and everything was full of flavor.

Amazing dinner! Chef Tony's is now open for dining in, with appropriate social distancing measures in place. The food was delicious. Everything we ordered was absolutely perfect. We ordered lobster and branzini and both were to die for. The appetizers and desserts were also superb. We will return soon. This is my new favorite restaurant in the area.
Great food and service! Dad's Crab Pasta was excellent and creme brulee and tiramisu hit the spot!
Great spot for a big lobster! love the cheesy Goldfish tank
Great lobster and good wine!

With relatives coming in from out of town, we wanted to have a "wine pairing" dinner.  Not wanting to go to downtown DC, Chef Tony';s was a convenient location with a parking garage across the street. We did schedule this dinner several weeks in advance, and finalized the menu and pairings beforehand (They provided a menu tailored just for us). We were seated promptly, and the service was exceptional, as well as the food! (see pictures).  We had plenty of time, and were not rushed at all. The servers explained each food and wine selection in detail.  Everything was fresh and cooked to perfection. We met Chef Tony and his wife afterward, and they were charming and appreciative of our patronage. Well done, Chef Tony and Staff!  UPDATE, June 2020 We ordered takeout from Chef Tony's for a 60th Birthday party for 12 People.  I volunteered to pick up dinner, and pulled up to chef Tony's, where the spot outside the restaurant was reserved for pickup orders.  I was pleased to note that the young man working outside had a mask and gloves, in addition to the chef's apron!  (I am keenly aware of Properly worn PPE and respect when people in the food service industry "get it right").  He pulled the order quickly, and  placed it in the car for me without incident.  Everything was hot and ready when I arrived at the party 10 minutes later!  All the food was delicious, and there were ample napkins and plastic silverware.  I was very impressed, and pleased at the extra steps taken in preparation.  I also learned that chef Tony's has been "deep cleaned" for cleanliness as well.  normally we would have gone to the restaurant,  but our outdoor "social distancing party" was a success!  Kudos to Chef Tony and his staff for doing a great job!
Grilled salmon and crispy plantains were EXCELLENT. Service was great. Can't wait to go back.

I love this restaurant! They offer marvelous dishes, their menu is varied, The cook in that place is very trained, I love a lot trying all their food. The dishes are always good, the attitude towards the clients  is very good too. I  go often to this restaurant and I was never unhappy. I recommend it to all my friends.
I ordered delivery and payed $130 for 4 dishes and $20 for the service fee. The food came in small sized portions for almost $30 each and didn't taste great. This was first and last time.
An absolutely fantastic restaurant! Food and service is always excellent! Been coming here for years! Chef Tony is awesome!

I had the Crab soup, it was good but had a little too much old bay seasoning. The filet mignon satay was delish! Grilled shrimp was also great! The fried calamari was crispy, fresh and melts in your mouth! I’d probably ad more breading, but that’s me. The crepe brûlée was good as well. The owners even sent me a follow up email the next day! What a great place in local Bethesda Maryland

two days ago was our first time we came to that magnificent restaurant. But It is obviously not the last. We had great time with the excellent service, with the fine  meal and fine drinks and with the modest price. We will definitely go back there again.
Well-prepared food, good service & 1/2 price wine on Sundays!
The customer service is regularly speedy, lovely atmosphere, very welcoming employees. Will visit here again when I get here.
Great food, great service. First time customer see you soon . Nice of you to introduce yourself Tony as well.
Great food !
This is one of my 2 favorite restaurants. The food is always fresh and delicious and Chefs Tony and Sonya are fantastic!

Firsr time visiting the restaurant and we were very impressed.  Food was delicious and everything was full of flavor.  We had Scallops, Mussels, and Shrimp appetizers with the Dad's Crab Pasta for the entree.  Warm treatment by the staff as well.  Will be back next time we're in Bethesda!!  Thanks for a great meal.
great location. traditional menus and I hear the sauces are phenomenal
Very well kept and welcoming restaurant. They provide big meals and for reasonable rates. We liked the food a lot and the waiters were super welcoming and chatty. I recommend this place.

Food was outstanding! Seafood paella and stuffed crabmeat mushrooms (appetizer) were delicious! Service was friendly, timely. Atmosphere was intimate and right noise level for conversation. Highly recommend.
Best seafood in the area

Tonight I had the seafood stew and it was delicious as always.  it was very tasty but it did seem to have less broth/gravy than the last time and did seem to be less filling but I'll definitely order it again. They added more pepper as requested because I prefer it with a little more kick. This is my favorite restaurant in Bethesda and as always I can't wait to come back next time in in town.  Very fresh seafood!
Service, perfect:; Food, perfect; Wine, exceptionally perfect.
The place offers a large range of fresh food. I loved eating here. The employees are always super nice, rates are affordable and the spot is always kept clean.

Delightful surprise of succulent, seafood and other tasty perfectly prepared dishes, mixed drinks and desserts! We've just found our new go-to restaurant! Fantastic food & attentive, timely & friendly, informative wait staff!
The meals was great and the prices were worth it. Quick, efficient service and very amiable waiters. Kudos!
Small place but excelent food and service
Excellent food and service. A real find in Bethesda.

Chef Tony’s is one of my personal favorite seafood restaurants in the area. Chef Tony’s has an amazing 3-course menu option (Appetizer, Entree, Dessert). The food is very delicious with nice portions. The service is exceptional and very down-to-earth. The staff really care about their customers and continue to add personal connections to the guests experiences. The owner is also very nice and welcoming to new customers or reoccurring locals. The five times I’ve been to this restaurant, the food is exceedingly consistent and always tastes good. I would highly recommend coming to this place with anyone or everyone. The quality, experience, people, and food is unforgettable and definitely worth it! Thanks so much Chef Tony...

It is the best restaurant i have ever had the pleasure of enjoying. I can not say enough great things about Tony's. Run don't walk the food dances in your mouth. Want to work my way through the menu. 😋
Delicious every single time. And reasonably priced, too.

From the first moment  you enter that place  they give you an excellent feeling. Very comfortable hosts, it is a friendly place to  pass time with your friends or with your date. tasty  cooking, creative  chef de cuisine, comfortable  cost and excellent  service. Highly recommended.
This place simply knows how to take care of their clients. Consistently with a very welcoming approach. The food is fairly priced, regularly delightful and clean.

The personal attention to their customers. Chef Tony is amazing at cooking sea food! Best Scallops I've EVER HAD! LOBSTER melt in your mouth great! Exceptional taste in each and every dish. Make reservations, or get there right when they open!
One of the most topnotch restaurants in Bethesda.  Brilliant food. The seafoods and desserts are really delectable.
Small and intimate atmosphere. The food is awesome,  which is what it's all about. Don't pass this one up!
The place serves big portions and for affordable rates. friendly staff. Great work.
The place is excellent and spacious, the meals was delightful and the prices were very inexpensive. quickly, efficient service and very amiable waiters. Highly recommended.
Fresh seafood is the word of the day.... always fresh
Host was rude. Food was too heavy with cream. Mandatory 18% charge of the original price on menu was not disclosed on voucher. Waiter was nice.
Good food. Authentic. A little noisy and tight but that’s part of the authenticity. Great staff

As a foodie, I have enjoyed eating at Chef'Tony's for many years. When I had a milestone birthday earlier this year, I reached to Chef Tony to plan the catering for 65 people. To this day, I get compliments on the food from my guests. Chef Tony helped organize the full catering service including staff and worked with my budget to make my special day memorable.
Luv the food. Great atmosphere.
The very BEST restaurant in all Maryland and Washington DC and Northern Virginia area and hands down the BEST CHEF i know 💯% 👍
Chef Tony's is what a restaurant should be.  The food is beyond delicious, and the service is old-school classy. Don't miss out on the crab cake -- it's the best I've had in decades!
Loved the food. Great atmosphere.
Food and service was good. I didn't give 5 stars because waiter repeatedly made mistakes on the bill. The maitre d' finally had to step in to give us a correct bill.
He was great and the food was a work of art
Wonderful fresh seafood served by caring staff who appreciate a special evening out. Good food in a comfortable setting. The small room off to the side is great for a romantic dinner for two.

Delicious food and great service.  I hosted the rehearsal dinner for my wedding here, and all of the guests loved it. Chef Tony personally worked with us to create a menu with options we wanted that was within our budget. The host, Steve, made sure all of our guest's needs were attended to.

This place is amazing. From the appetizer to dessert, everything was delicious. Great service, price, and portions. Try the arnold palmer and bread. You won't be disappointed with your menu choices. Definitely a great date night spot.

This was visited on the special occasion of my fathers birthday!!!  We chose this based on the great reviews of others.  I nor my family was disappointed.  The food and service was excellent.   I would definitely return again when in this area.  Parking is a little difficult however there is a parking garage right across the street.  Although nothing stands out from the entrance there was little doubt the locals know about the excellent food as it got pretty busy.  We went on there lobster special evening which brought many people.  We all ordered and different plates and loved all of the entrees!!!
Good food, friendly service!
Great service and good
Great food! Courteous and friendly service. Definitely worth a try.
Food was fantastic.
Amazing people that genuinely care about your experience!
The food was great but the dessert was the star of the evening.

Soo.... the kids are away and since we had a few more days to play... We came by Chef Tony's. AMAAAZINGG!! I've been searching all over for the Calamari that I had at The Breakers in West Palm Beach years ago and LORD!! Topped that! EVERYTHING WAS TASTY/DELICIOUS and fresh! Seafood FOODIE!! Chef Tony was very personable.
Dinner was so delicious. Had the halibut topped with crab. Loved it! :-)
Amazing place, amazing food, amazing people. Must visit!

Absolutely Fabulous! My friend and I had the Zucchini for appetizer & crabcake for dinner, absolutely the best food ever. Do not skip eating here, it would be your loss. Service was also fantastic, we didn't have reservation, but they were able to accommodate us.
Best  clamaria I ever ateclams so good and will come back
Calamari w half-price wine at bar
The food is constantly fresh and yummy, workers gives excellent customer service. I loved how clean it is and mood. Highly recommended.
The food is incredible and cooked perfectly. You cannot be disappointed.
Decent seafood and good service
This place knows how to take care of their clients. Regularly with a very welcoming attitude. The food is affordably priced, always delightful and neat.
Server / Chase recommended tasty items for our first visit.  Calamari was very good.  Entrees included Crab Pasta and Scallops and both were also very good.
This spot is excellent! Affordable pricing, considerable dishes and the staff are always very friendly.

Great food, especially the Bronzino and Creme Brûlée, but terrible service.  My husband and I returned to Chef Tony’s after a great first experience.  This evening, however, was the far opposite and we were here to celebrate our anniversary.  We were never offered bread and when we asked about specials the waiter opened the menu and said “here”, my water glass sat empty most of the meal, etc.  The list goes on.   I was saddened by this experience and would hope for better service for $30/meal.

Food: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️🙂 Costumer Service: ⭐️⭐️☹️  All I have to say is this restaurant; has amazing cooking. Haven’t been disappointed. Now the customer service needs some improving on. My mother’s birthday 🎂 was today and we didn’t feel our service was made special. No candle for dessert. Not very attentive to our needs and wants. The food was amazing!!! Dessert 🍨 wonderful!
I always stop by buying some food here. I enjoy the swift customer service and well prepared food. Great work.

Bought a Living Social deal for this establishment, and I was very pleased with the food and service. Chef Tony came from the kitchen at some point during our meal and walked around greeting quest. Loved it!
Everything we had was excellent! If you're into 3 courses, there's a Groupon that's a good deal! ...or take home leftovers.

Always a top pick if you're in the mood for seafood. Outstanding calamari and as delicious as everything is on the menu, it is very difficult to not indulge in Chef's Daily specials; always fresh, seasonal and memorable.
A great family restaurant where the food is superb
First time at Chef Tony’s and the food was wonderful. The best meal we have had in Bethesda!!
Its a gem.  5 meals here in the past 12 months and all very very good. Make reservations and try the crab ANYTHING.  Can be a little noisy, so not conducive to lingering, but the food is great.
Very good food and very good service.   Items are a little pricey and restaurant a/c couldn't keep up with the heat
Better to make reservations but they will accommodate walk-ins if they can.
The food here is amazing and due to the time of day we got to interact with Chef Tony. He also has a dish of pasta that donates $2 to charity for kids. The staff is friendly and patient.
Excellent restaurant. Great food, top service. Loved the half-price wine Tuesday. Paid $80 for a bottle-of-wine dinner with dessert for two. Quality + VALUE!!!
This was a great meal with some amazing seafood. The lobster was buttery goodness. The scallops were great... According to my coworker.
Amazing
Food was ok, presentation was bad.  Service was very slow - need to try to make it three times faster.  I will not be going back there.
Amazing ambience and the food was seafood was fresh and delicious! We will be back!!!

I was meeting my son from New Mexico who was in Virginia on business and I was in northern Maryland. I tried to find a halfway point for us to meet,  but traffic would have tied him up over 1 1/2 hours to meet me. I was already at the middle point and ChefTony's was one of my searches. So we met at Tony's. Our service was excellent and everything was so tastefully prepared. I brought home half of my meal and the left-overs I ate were just as delightful as the night before. I will definitely come again. The atmosphere was perfect for us to talk and catch up on things. It was a perfect night for me. thanks, Chef Tony.
Excellent service, nicely presented.
Always spectacular!
The food was very good and the fish was sweet. The service was a little slow but a very nice server.
Excellent food. Service, not so much.
Food and service were both excellent. Chase, our server, highly recommended the grilled Cesar salad and he was absolutely right. Fabulous!
Surprisingly good. Calamari is amazing, lettuce salad is also surprisingly good. I ordered mignon satay, best I have ever had!
Best bisque around
Excellent fresh seafood.  I especially love the seafood stew and the monkfish when it is available.  Every meal I've had at Chef Tony's has been superb.

Outstanding choice for fresh seafood in Bethesda!
Best restaurant in the DMV area. Their spicey shrimp pasta is amazing. Also, you really can't go wrong with any of their other meals. This place is a must when you go to Bathesda.
A very friendly environment with a very good food

Nice place. The fish was perfectly cooked and tasted great!!

Food was very good, but the service was impeccable!
Small place, recommend reservations. Really great food.
The food was very well prepared and reasonable for such great quality. I suggest making reservations and prepare yourself to park in the garage located across from the establishment!!..👍
Very friendly service and tasty food. My dish was great but my companion felt it was lacking.  Still worth a trip and the muscles are delicious.
Always delicious food and top quality service. One of my favorites.

Great tasting food, friendly staff. While it's a bit more money it's well worth it. Reservations are in order as their seating is limited. Easy parking right across the street. Free on the weekend but pay on the weekdays.
Great

If you want a good food in a nice ambiance, you can come to this restaurant. However, PLEASE do not come as a party of two. You will be seated in a very narrow corridor like a jail. My friend and I sat in front of the door that goes to the kitchen and had to endure the noise of dishes all over the place. My right arm was brushing the wall so my purse had to be on the chair near the corridor. It was dropped 3 times by the waiter that had very tight space to walk. I had no choice other than put my purse on the floor under the little table that could barely hold our plates. I ordered jumbo scallops and got seafood paella. Not my favorite but I accepted it otherwise I would had to endure a lot mire time at the torture corridor. The price was really high, not worth what we got. The service was really bad too.  Bottom line: I will never go back, unless I go with a large group and be seated in a good place.  Sent from my iPhone
Delicious food.
Excellent!

Great food!
Exceptional culinary experience and the entire staff is phenomenal, makes you feel right at home.  A must if you're in the area ..
The food and service was great! Would definitely come back and recommend.

Very pleasant surprise. We're new to the neighborhood and now we see why this is a Bethesda favorite. Service was slow to start but sufficient through the rest of the meal. The whole snapper was excellent!!

I love the service.  The maitre d is engaging and warm.  The waiters are accommodating. The menu is nice .  The food is flavorful.  The fish and calamari is FRESH.  This is how dining out should be.  Also, great tramitsu and cheesecake!

Food is just amazing, if you are expecting fancy this is not your place but if you want quality real food with great service and atmosphere this is for you. Glad to see Chef Tony working there everyday and always taking care of his food, employees and patrons. The service is as good as their food. Prices for portion are excellent, 100% recommended.
The food is always great:
This is an awesome date place. Food is great, cozy atmosphere, and friendly service. Grilled Romain lettuce and the calamari are a must have.
As usual Chef Tony's did not disappoint. Food was on point just needed to tweak the service.

Love this place! It's local which is great, but it's an unsuspecting place that one might not think served excellent seafood. I ordered the surf and turf, my husband ordered the braised cod. Let me just say that the worst things on our plates were the potatoes, and those were good too! Jumbo scallops were perfectly done, and the shrimp, fillet, and cod followed suit. The tiramisu was different from any I've had, but I enjoyed it because there was a higher ratio of Lady fingers to cream than normal. Paired with an Americano coffee, the dessert ended a fantastic experience. The server, who coincidentally was also named Anthony, was polite and timely. Not too expensive+ good service+ amazing food= we will be returning soon.
Fantastic!!!
Excellent communication and flexibility for large groups.
Great little place with excellent food and service

The food we ordered was just simply awesome. We had the cream of crab soup, the crab cake meal and the seafood stew, followed by Tiramisu!  All of it was just out of this world.  Atmosphere there is perfect!  We are going to be back when we are in this area!

Have been wanting to try Chef Tony for some time. Had 4 hours to kill in Bethesda Saturday night and they were able to fit me in a 7:45 reservation. Wow the menu is big and so many quality choices to choose from. The grilled ceasar is big but has so much flavor and the cream of crab soup was heavy but worth every spoon full. My main course was the Tuna featured in the picture it was excellent. I look forward to coming back so many more things to try.
Love this place! I try to visit every time I come to Bethesda, MD. Great food and friendly staff.
Wow!!! Great restaurant!! Definitely make reservations.
Fresh and tasty food with daily specials. Excellent service and ambience. We have had wonderful meals here many times.

To be fair this is about customer experience and not about food. I was visiting the area and when in Maryland you gotta have crab cakes so that was the plan for this visit. The picture of the food looks great and this place has great reviews.  Now my experience. The place is tiny so expect a wait. I was fine with that. There really isnt any place to wait either if you decide to stay. Again not a big deal for me. So I waited and then I noticed two tables get sat before me which is a problem. It's not like they were waiting because they weren't. I decided to leave which is to bad because I'm from out of town and doubtful that I would visit the area again. I had to get the crab cake at my hotel which was fine but I had high hopes to visit Tony's.

Did not like it.  The taste was okay. Did not like the way we were greeted.  When we got to the restaurant,  I said, "we have a reservation for 4 at 6pm". And the Greeting person greeted us this way, "Do you have a name or do i keep guessing?". Our family thought, that was rude.  And he showed us and the other people the table at the same time by pointing at it.  He didn't even seat us properly.
Got a LivingSocial voucher for three-prix menu. Food was fantastic! Crab soup, Wow! Crab & pasta delicious! Sweet potatoe dessert was a great ending to the meal. Will definitely go back!

I started with the braised portabella mushrooms with red wine, reduced balsamic vinegar, and greens.  It was one of thoes appetizers that was so good, you wouldn't mind ordering a larger version as a meal. Delicious. The mushrooms were sliced and tossed with the greens, soaking in the delicious wine and balsamic dressing with fresh garlic and herbs. The portabella mushrooms were tender and flavorful,  not too soft and not rubbery - perfectly prepared.  My wife had the roasted carrot soup,  which was deceivingly comforting and sweet. Reminiscent of pumpkin soup, but fluffier.  The first time the waiter suggested it she was apprehensive,  but once she tried it, she never looked back and it has now become her destination go-to starter.  She then had the shredded crab and spiral pasta, which she tells me was delicious,  but the soup filled her up and she brought most of it home, so I'm sure I'll be having that for lunch tomorrow.   And I has the chicken marsala, which came with linguini and more of thoes succulent mushrooms.  The crushed tomatoe sauce was very well seasoned and of perfect consistency, but the chicken could have used a touch more salt and about 1 minute less time  in the pan, but when paired with the pasta and sauce, it made a great and flavorful bite.  We were seated in a little cove in the restaurant called Lover's Lane, which was perfect because it kept the usual restaurant chatter noise down and was lit up very nicely with string lights on the walls and nicely painted murals.  Finally, I splurged and couldn't stop eating the warm banana, cranberry, and apple bread pudding with warm vanilla Jack Daniels sauce, topped with vanilla ice cream. Trust me, it was EXACTLY as good as it sounds.  Again, always a treat.

I have visited Chef Tony's a few times over the past year. It is a small restaurant with big dreams and the food reflects a drive for notice within the Bethesda area.  /Food/ Appetizer: Of the appetizers I have tried over the course of my visits [some being sampled from my SO's plate](Tapas sampler, mussels, calamari, crispy zucchini, ceviche, carrot soup, and a crap soup), I enjoyed the mussels and crab soup the most. The mussels were fresh and served in a delicious warm broth with bread and the crap soup had lumps of crab in a creamy base. I wish I had a spoon for the mussel broth!  Entree: As a seafood restaurant, the 3-course prix-fixe doesn't have any steak or red-meat listings but boasts salmon dishes, cod, monkfish, chicken dishes, and a few others I cannot recall. My personal favorite entree is the Scottish Salmon served with plantains and a cucumber salad, served medium-rare.  The comment about "big dreams" applies to the entree dishes I have sampled mainly because of lack of consistency, i.e. they are still experimenting with the dishes? The fish is fresh and perfectly cooked, however, the portions and servings have varied across my visits. E.g.: one time I had 4 plantains piled on the plate w/ my salmon order and then next there were 3 artfully arranged plantains, propped up for display; the cucumber salad on the side versus under the fish, etc. Consistently delicious, just variability in plating/serving makes me think there is still some experimentation with how the restaurant wants to present itself (and their food).  Dessert: About half of the desserts on the menu are made by Chef Tony's wife. The ones I have sampled pick directly from the house-made desserts which include cheesecake w/walnut crust, creme brulee, and tiramisu. Cheesecake: very, very rich. My significant other confided that they dream about the cheesecake at Chef Tony's because of the walnut crust. I was pleasantly surprised about how nutty and delicious the crust was with the chunky walnuts adding a nice texture to the thick cheesecake, however, I find the cheesecake very heavy and dense and the crust can be hard to cut through at times. Delicious, but again, consistency across visits has some crusts thicker than others. Served w/ strawberries, blackberries, and a sprig of mint on the side that helped constrast the creamy cheesecake. Creme brulee: perfect. served w/ strawberries, beautifully bruleed and flecks of vanilla bean throughout. Tirimisu: fluffy and creamy with a generous amount of cocoa powder dusting the top. Definitely something to split.  /Atmosphere/ The servers and Chef Tony have a family-like camaraderie that makes dining pleasant as all the servers are friendly and willing to help each other. The dining room is an odd shape with an alley like stretch of two-person tables walled up to the right of the entrance, a small area of tables upon walking in, and another dining room towards the back near the kitchen door. The two main dining areas are connected by a stretch that passes the semi-open kitchen/bar area. Chef Tony can been seen through the semi-open kitchen and often greets guests as they walk through. The decor is an odd mashup of Spanish-inspired and homey-chatskis that make the dining room causal and unpretentious. Also separating the dining spaces is a transition from wood in the entry-way dining area and tile in the back area. I would love to see a layout overhaul of the dining room area to unify and update the interior but the home-y-ness adds to it's charm.  /Price/ Reasonable for the Bethesda area (~$17-$25 for dinner entree, $35 for 3 course prix-fixe) and so many promotions and loyalty programs in frequent rotation. Chef Tony sends out an email letter if you sign up w/ deal promotions.  Overall, I enjoy the whole experience at Chef Tony's more than the individual dissection of its parts. The fresh seafood is wonderful but the combination of relaxed atmosphere with the friendliness of the staff make it a nice evening spot in the bustle of downtown Bethesda i.e. 5 stars.

Went in at the height of lunch hour in Bethesda to find the place deserted. I should have taken that as the first clue. The food was cold and tasteless. I ordered fish as the place seemed to be trying to stake themselves as a seafood restaurant. Blech and blech.  How this place is *still* open is beyond me.

This place is pretty bad. I went here with my girlfriend as part of the $25 living social three course meal for two coupon. The meal started off pretty good. For appetizer we got the calamari and mussels. Mussels were very well cooked and calamari was equally as tasty.  The entree round fell flat on its face. The sole was decent, but everything else on the plate was just mushed together. I had the monkfish, which was terribly overcooked and tasted nothing like it was supposed to. The veggies were soggy and the broth probably could have used a little less salt.  Then came the dessert round. I've never had anything more disgusting in my life. The tiramisu tasted like it had fell in the toilet. It was extremely soggy and there was barely any flavor. The sweet potato pie was done like a creme brulee, but it too was watery and did not appeal to my taste buds.  Needless to say I will not be coming here again. If you want to waste $50 of your own money feel free.

Came to Chef Tony's for the first time with a groupon.  Groups of 6 of us and 1 baby.  The staff was super friendly and accomodating! Some our favorties: the calamari, seafood crevieche, crab soup for starters; organic poached salmon over pasta for entree; creme brulee, sweet potato pie, and tira misu for dessert; house mojito, red stag honey bourbon for drinks. Everything was fresh and delicious.  Will definitely come again.
Was there for lunch, great food and affordable price. Really surprised by the quality.

I rarely write good reviews for anything but I thought this restaurant deserved a positive rave.  The service was great, our waiter was very cordial and knowledgeable about the menu.  I ordered the Filet Mignon Tapas dish which was cooked to perfection along with the calamari.  My date ordered the crabcake and I had the shrimp and lobster pasta which was absolutely delicious.  The portions are pretty large and given the quality, the price is an absolute steal.  Everything tasted extremely fresh and I was really pleased with my entire dining experience.  I would definitely visit again and will recommend this quaint little spot to others.

We have eaten a couple times here. The latest time was strange.  We got a nice table right away with our small child, who they were very warm with.  Although it wasn't crowded, we waited 20 minutes for our starters. I had ordered the filet mignon satays rare; they arrived well done. They were replaced almost immediately with a small apology.  For my main I ordered scallops partly because they were supposed to be served with mashed potatoes, which I had been craving.  But then they arrived with lentils! There was no offer to switch it out.  Explanation at the end of the meal was that Chef Tony made a mistake. The food, including the lentils, was delicious.  However, there were mistakes and the service was a little too slow.
